      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"targeted accommodations\" sounds like a way for the state to decide which religions are \"okay\" and which ones aren't. basically, the government gets to pick and choose who gets to listen to their conscience based on whatever the state thinks is \"reasonable.\" isn't that just a slippery slope toward the state controlling all religious expression? why should the government's version of \"social order\" always come before a person's soul?",
